{
  "text": "DQ and DQH 2 were previously demonstrated to have free access to the regions representing the cells and the medium (3), i.e., the concentrations of DQ and DQH 2 at the intracellular reaction sites are essentially in equilibrium with their respective medium concentrations. With the use of mass balance and mass action, the temporal variations in the concentrations of the various species in medium or cell region are described in Eqs. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Fig. 7 . Immunoblots of normoxic and hyperoxia-exposed cell NQO1. The image is a composite of 5 immunoblots obtained using 5 different sets of normoxic (N) and hyperoxia-exposed (H) cell cultures. The same amount of cytosolic protein was loaded onto the gels for each normoxic and hyperoxiaexposed set (6 g for pairs in A and B and 3 g of protein for pairs in C-E).",
